HEADWORD: Pig-headed
<hw>Pig"-head`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a head
like a pig; hence, figuratively: stupidity obstinate; perverse;
stubborn.</def> <au>B. Jonson.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Pig"-head`ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

